        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - Analogous estimating is a top-down technique used when detailed information is lacking. While useful for early, rough estimates, the scenario provides specific historical productivity rates, which allow for a more precise calculation than a high-level comparison to a similar project.",
        "option_c_result": "CORRECT - Parametric estimating involves using a statistical relationship between historical data and other variables to calculate an estimate. In this case, the relationship is the rate of meters of road per operator per week. Given the historical data of 500 meters/operator/week and the total length of 2500 meters, the project manager can directly calculate (2500 / 500 = 5 operators needed per week) the required number of operators, making this the most accurate and efficient approach.",
